\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces End-to-end dual-signal SBFL pipeline for NL-to-FOL knowledge base repair. Stage\nobreakspace  {}1 extracts a Prolog KB from natural language via LLM. Stage\nobreakspace  {}2 generates a localization oracle (yes/no queries used only for repair targeting, not evaluation). Stage\nobreakspace  {}3 runs a stratified coverage spectrum, distinguishing direct-fault predicates (failed to unify) from indirect-fault predicates (unified, sub-goals failed) and harvesting deepest unsatisfied sub-goals. Stage\nobreakspace  {}4 computes dual suspiciousness rankings (Ochiai + sub-goal frequency). Stage\nobreakspace  {}5 performs targeted LLM repair on the top-$K$ suspicious items. Final evaluation uses human-annotated benchmark labels, decoupled from the localization oracle.}}{3}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:pipeline}{{1}{3}{End-to-end dual-signal SBFL pipeline for NL-to-FOL knowledge base repair. Stage~1 extracts a Prolog KB from natural language via LLM. Stage~2 generates a localization oracle (yes/no queries used only for repair targeting, not evaluation). Stage~3 runs a stratified coverage spectrum, distinguishing direct-fault predicates (failed to unify) from indirect-fault predicates (unified, sub-goals failed) and harvesting deepest unsatisfied sub-goals. Stage~4 computes dual suspiciousness rankings (Ochiai + sub-goal frequency). Stage~5 performs targeted LLM repair on the top-$K$ suspicious items. Final evaluation uses human-annotated benchmark labels, decoupled from the localization oracle}{figure.1}{}}
